entry.tran: 不太可能的；未必会发生的
entry.def: If you say that something is unlikely to happen or unlikely to be true, you believe that it will not happen or that it is not true, although you are not completely sure.

example.tran: 看起来不太可能会发生军事政变。

example.ex: As with many technological revolutions, you are unlikely to be aware of it...
example.tran: 就像诸多的技术革命一样，你可能不太会注意到它。

means.word_mean: 1. not likely to be true or to occur or to have occurred;

sentences.sentence: "legislation on the question is highly unlikely"

means.word_mean: 2. has little chance of being the case or coming about;

sentences.sentence: "a butcher is unlikely to preach vegetarianism"

means.word_mean: 3. having a probability to low to inspire belief

Sentence.sentence: A new technology is unlikely to take the place of an old one without a clear advantage.
Some version of the Swedish system might work well for a majority of American parents,but the United States is unlikely to fully embrace the Swedish model.
However, a further increase in farming area without impacting unfavourably on what remains of the world's natural ecosystems appears unlikely.
The predicted intergenerational warfare is unlikely because most of the older people themselves mostly have families.
